documentation_summary: The HTML text is a PyPI (Python Package Index) page for the "great-expectations" package, version 0.18.10, released on February 26, 2024. It includes a warning for users with unsupported browsers (IE9 and below) to upgrade for better compatibility. The package aims to help users have clear expectations from their data, requiring Python version 3.8 or higher. It is licensed under the Apache Software License (Apache-2.0) and is currently in beta development status. The package is intended for developers, scientists, and researchers involved in data science, testing, and quality assurance, offering features for data validation and quality checks.
